        "text": "*[Bug 19071] wilcox.test and precision when detecting zeros*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19071>\n\n--- Comment #5 from Martin Maechler (<mailto:maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch|maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch>) ---\n(In reply to caerolus from comment #4)\nTo the contrary:   All such tests should be location and scale invariant {well,\nalmost: as long as numbers don't come close to overflow or underflow}.\nround()ing requires the users to know the scale; `signif()` for the ranks is\ndefinitely correct here ... and `zapsmall()` *is* just calling `round()` but in\nscale-equivariant way.\n\nRemember that the users who know more about the numbers in their samples can of\ncourse use `round()` or `signif()` themselves and then possibly use `digits* =\nInf`, the current default, such that wilcox.test() would no further round.",
